wikipedia_page.main: William Hartley Carnegie (27 February 1859 – 18 October 1936) was an Anglican priest and author. In addition to parish ministries and chaplaincy, he served as Archdeacon of Westminster from 1918 to 1919 and as Sub-Dean of Westminster Abbey from 1919 to 1936.

response: * 1912–1936† William Hartley Carnegie (also Speaker's Chaplain from 1916)
